Class RelationContainer

  • java.lang.Object
    • au.edu.anu.twcore.ecosystem.runtime.system.RelationContainer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Container, DynamicContainer<SystemRelation>, Related<CategorizedComponent>, ObservableDynamicGraph<SystemComponent,​SystemRelation>, fr.cnrs.iees.identity.Identity, fr.cnrs.iees.rvgrid.observer.Observable<DynamicGraphObserver<SystemComponent,​SystemRelation>>, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Resettable
    public class RelationContainer
extends java.lang.Object
implements DynamicContainer<SystemRelation>, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Resettable, Related<CategorizedComponent>, ObservableDynamicGraph<SystemComponent,​SystemRelation>
    Management of relations (ie delayed addition and removal). this is NOT a container, i.e. relations are not stored here, they are stored by the SystemComponent edge lists.
    Author:
    Jacques Gignoux - 16 janv. 2020

      • effectChanges

        @SafeVarargs
public final void effectChanges​(java.util.Collection<SystemRelation>... changedLists)
        Description copied from interface: DynamicContainer
        Effectively remove and add items from the container lists (before a call to this method, they are just stored into itemsToRemove and itemsToAdd). NB: to recursively effect changes for all sub-containers, use effectAllChanges(). The arguments are here in case a return list of items is needed - depends on context of course
        Specified by:
        effectChanges in interface DynamicContainer<SystemRelation>
